Description:
   Cistern Discipline is a foundational conditioning practice shared by
   Pugilists and Sentinels. The warrior trains their body to absorb more
   punishment by hardening their constitution through focused physical
   conditioning regimens. While this discipline is active, the character
   gains increased hit point regeneration and improved stamina.

   The technique takes its name from the ancient training wells where fighters
   would practice endurance by treading water for hours. Modern practitioners
   use equivalent sustained physical drills to achieve the same metabolic
   conditioning. The effect improves survivability in extended fights by
   ensuring the warrior recovers between engagements.
